<doc f='llvm/clang/lib/Sema/SemaExprCXX.cpp' l='6453'>/// Find a merged pointer type and convert the two expressions to it.
///
/// This finds the composite pointer type for \p E1 and \p E2 according to
/// C++2a [expr.type]p3. It converts both expressions to this type and returns
/// it.  It does not emit diagnostics (FIXME: that&apos;s not true if \p ConvertArgs
/// is \c true).
///
/// \param Loc The location of the operator requiring these two expressions to
/// be converted to the composite pointer type.
///
/// \param ConvertArgs If \c false, do not convert E1 and E2 to the target type.</doc>
